#@title #Choose Dataset { run: "auto" }
df = list(datasets)
index =  3#@param {type:"integer"}
#@markdown Use keyword 'dataset' to access the dataset

#@markdown ---

#@markdown #Top Features
#@markdown Auto select top N features from dataset
topFeatures = 0 #@param {type:"integer"}
#@markdown Top features defined by me
myTopFeatures = '' #@param {type:"string"}
#@markdown \* Separate top features with comma (,)
#@markdown
#@markdown Use wildcard \* to select multiple features with the same prefix

from pprint import pprint
try:
  if index > 0 and index <= len(df):
    index -= 1
    title = df[index]
    dataset = datasets[df[index]]
    print("Dataset: {}\n".format(title))

    if topFeatures > 0 and topFeatures <= dataset.shape[1]:
      dataset, features = KBestFeatures(topFeatures,dataset)
      print("Top {} features\n".format(topFeatures))
      pprint(features)

    if myTopFeatures:    
      dataset, features = MyTopFeatures(myTopFeatures,dataset)
      print("Top {} features\n".format(len(features)))
      pprint(features)

    dataset = normalize(dataset, modelPrefix + 'StandardScaler' ) #<----

    print("\nTransforming dataset...\n")
    X_train, y_train, X_valid, y_valid, X_test, y_test = splitDataset(dataset)

    print("Analyzing dataset...\n")
    analyzeDataset(dataset, title)

    if not OHE:
      print("\n")
      getCorelationMatrix(X_train, title)
except Exception as e:
  print(str(e))

#@title Random Forest Classifier

if random_forest_classifier:
  print("\nRandom Forest Classifier\n")

  if OHE:
    hyperparameters = TreeBasedModelHyperparameterSelector(X_train, y_train, iteration=2, cross_val=3, randomForest=True, verbose_lvl=2)
  else:
    hyperparameters = TreeBasedModelHyperparameterSelector(X_train, y_train, randomForest=True, verbose_lvl=2)
  
  randomForestModel = RandomForestClassifier(**hyperparameters, n_jobs=-1)
  print("\n",randomForestModel)
  
  if selectTopFeatures:
    selected_features = SelectFromModel(randomForestModel)
    selected_features.fit(X_train, y_train)
    features = X_train.columns[(selected_features.get_support())]
    X_train_randForest = selected_features.transform(X_train)
    X_test_randForest = selected_features.transform(X_test)
    X_valid_randForest = selected_features.transform(X_valid)
    print("\nSelected features: {}".format(features))

    hyperparameters = TreeBasedModelHyperparameterSelector(X_train_randForest, y_train, randomForest=True, verbose_lvl=2)
    randomForestModel = RandomForestClassifier(**hyperparameters, n_jobs=-1)
    print("\n",randomForestModel)
    randomForest = randomForestModel.fit(X_train_randForest, y_train)
    acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr = predict(randomForest, X_valid_randForest, y_valid,"Validation set prediction")
    acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr = predict(randomForest, X_test_randForest, y_test,"Test set prediction")
  else:
    randomForest = randomForestModel.fit(X_train, y_train)
    acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr = predict(randomForest, X_valid, y_valid,"Validation set prediction")
    acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr = predict(randomForest, X_test, y_test,"Test set prediction")
    
  models = extendModels(models,'Random Forest Classifier',acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr)
  saveModel(randomForest, modelPrefix + 'RandomForest' + selectTopFeatures_sufix)
  saveModel(models, modelPrefix + 'Models', json=True)

#@title LSTM Neural Network

#@markdown Settings

neural_network_model = 'LSTM'
BATCH_SIZE = 128 #@param {type:"integer"}
EPOCHS = 100 #@param {type:"integer"}
PATIENCE = 5
lstm_heperparameter_tuning = True #@param {type:"boolean"}

if neural_network:
  print("\n", neural_network_model, "Neural Network\n")
  
  def LSTM(units=256, batch_size=128, dropout=0.1, init='random_uniform', lstm_activation='tanh', activation='sigmoid', optimizer='rmsprop'):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential()
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.LSTM(units, input_shape=(X_train_t.shape[1], X_train_t.shape[2]), kernel_initializer=init, activation=lstm_activation, recurrent_dropout=float(dropout/2), return_sequences=True))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.LSTM(units, kernel_initializer=init, activation=lstm_activation, recurrent_dropout=float(dropout/2), return_sequences=False))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Activation(activation))
    model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['acc'])
    return model

  grid = {'init': ['glorot_uniform', 'random_normal', 'lecun_uniform'], 
          'optimizer':['rmsprop', 'adadelta', 'nadam'],
          'lstm_activation': ['tanh', 'selu', 'relu', 'sigmoid'],
          'activation': ['tanh', 'selu', 'relu', 'sigmoid'],
          'dropout': [0.4, 0.3, 0.2],
          'batch_size': [128, 256, 512],
          'units': [64, 128, 256]}
  
  X_train_t = np.reshape(X_train.values, (X_train.shape[0], 1, X_train.shape[1]))
  X_valid_t = np.reshape(X_valid.values, (X_valid.shape[0], 1, X_valid.shape[1]))
  X_test_t = np.reshape(X_test.values, (X_test.shape[0], 1, X_test.shape[1]))

  if lstm_heperparameter_tuning:
    iteration = 2
    cross_val = 5
    model_KC = KerasClassifier(build_fn=LSTM, epochs=10, verbose=1)
    param_search = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator = model_KC, param_distributions = grid, n_iter = iteration, cv = cross_val, n_jobs=-1, verbose = 2)
    param_result = param_search.fit(X_train_t, y_train)
    print('\nBest Accuracy for %.2f%%\n%s' % (param_result.best_score_*100,param_result.best_params_))
    init = param_result.best_params_['init']
    optimizer = param_result.best_params_['optimizer']
    lstm_activation = param_result.best_params_['lstm_activation']
    activation = param_result.best_params_['activation']
    dropout = param_result.best_params_['dropout']
    units = param_result.best_params_['units']
    BATCH_SIZE = param_result.best_params_['batch_size']
    nn_model = LSTM(units=units, dropout=dropout, init=init, lstm_activation=lstm_activation, activation=activation, optimizer=optimizer)
  else:
    nn_model = LSTM()

  terminateOnNaN = TerminateOnNaN()
  lr = LearningRateScheduler(scheduler)
  reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', mode='auto', factor=0.01, patience=PATIENCE-2, cooldown=1, min_lr=0.001)
  early_stop = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=PATIENCE, mode='auto', restore_best_weights=True)
  checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath=machine_learning_models_path + modelPrefix + neural_network_model + '.h5', save_best_only=True, save_weights_only=False, mode='auto')
  callback = [early_stop, checkpoint, lr, reduce_lr, terminateOnNaN]
  nn_model_history = nn_model.fit(X_train_t, y_train, epochs=EPOCHS, validation_data=(X_valid_t, y_valid), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, validation_split=0.2, callbacks=callback, verbose=1)

  trainingHistoryVisualization(nn_model_history, neural_network_model)
  acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr = predictNN(nn_model, X_test_t, y_test,"Test set prediction")
  
  models = extendModels(models,neural_network_model,acc,f1,auc,fpr,tpr)
  plotModel(nn_model, modelPrefix + neural_network_model)
  #saveModel(nn_model, modelPrefix + neural_network_model, h5=True)
  saveModel(models, modelPrefix + 'Models', json=True)
  path = machine_learning_models_path + modelPrefix + neural_network_model + '.h5'
  nn_model.save(path)

if neural_network:
  print("\nRecurrent Neural Network\n")

  def RNN(units=256, batch_size=128, dropout=0.1, init='random_uniform', rnn_activation='tanh', activation='sigmoid', optimizer='rmsprop'):
    model = tf.keras.Sequential() 
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.SimpleRNN(units, input_shape=(X_train_t.shape[1], X_train_t.shape[2]), kernel_initializer=init, activation=rnn_activation, recurrent_dropout=float(dropout/2), return_sequences=True))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.SimpleRNN(units, input_shape=(X_train_t.shape[1], X_train_t.shape[2]), kernel_initializer=init, activation=rnn_activation, recurrent_dropout=float(dropout/2), return_sequences=False))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1))
    model.add(tf.keras.layers.Activation(activation))
    print(model.summary())
    model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['acc'])
    return model

  grid = {'init': ['glorot_uniform', 'random_normal', 'lecun_uniform'], 
          'optimizer':['rmsprop', 'adadelta', 'nadam'],
          'rnn_activation': ['tanh', 'selu', 'relu', 'sigmoid'],
          'activation': ['tanh', 'selu', 'relu', 'sigmoid'],
          'dropout': [0.4, 0.3, 0.2],
          'batch_size': [128, 256, 512],
          'units': [64, 128, 256]}
  
  X_train_t = np.reshape(X_train.values, (X_train.shape[0], 1, X_train.shape[1]))

    model_KC = KerasClassifier(build_fn=RNN, epochs=10, verbose=1)
    param_search = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator = model_KC, param_distributions = grid, n_iter = iteration, cv = cross_val, n_jobs=-1, verbose = 2)
    param_result = param_search.fit(X_train_t, y_train)
    print('\nBest Accuracy for %.2f%%\n%s' % (param_result.best_score_*100,param_result.best_params_))

    nn_model = RNN(units=units, dropout=dropout, init=init, rnn_activation=rnn_activation, activation=activation, optimizer=optimizer)
